                 div(class="c-cardGreen")
                        div(class="c-cardGreenContent u-textColor_1-darker lh30")
                            p There are many ways to offer help in English. Here are a few.
                            .mt20.lh20
                                p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] May I help you? Or can I help you?

                            .mt20
                                p These are usually used to offer help to someone when they look lost or confused.

                            .mt20.lh20
                                p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] After seeing the man wandering around the lobby the receptionist said, “Good afternoon, sir. May I help you find someone?” Are you looking for something?
                            .mt20
                                p This expression is usually used in stores by assistants trying to help customers.

                            .mt20.lh20
                                p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] The store assistant observed the man looking at the kitchenware. She walked over to him and said, “Hi, are you looking for something in particular?” What can I do for you today?
                            .mt20
                                p This is usually used to greet clients and offer assistance.

                            .mt20.lh20
                                p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] e.g. Good morning, sir. What can I do for you today?
                            .mt20
                                p Questions used to offer assistance: Do you need any help? Need any help? May I offer my assistance?

